column5: Fished for 2 hours! Didn't mark one fish but pulled wire in crystal clear water that was smooth like glass.  It was great to get out and scratch the itch.   Only came in becaues the ice told me too.
Always fun dodging iceburgs. At least you got out.
is it just me or is there a problem with photos on the site?
Fishfinder its not just you I have not been able to open those thumb nails either.MTP

nice to see ya got out today it was a great day.  I also dont care for the NEW set up for pics on the site it makes me not want to check most pics out when you have to wait for them to laod I am having flashbacks from dial up days
Only a few days till spring Derek. Won't be long now
WOW, looks like you had a great day...
I got a warning not to  open file.  Larry

The nails don't work for me either.  Before you post your pics, make sure it's the full picture on you computer when you copy the properties. Than it will come up full on your post, instead of the thumbs.

yes i got a warning about those pics as well..  ...it must have felt nice to get out in the boat...i cant wait im going crazy  ,i need to get my boat out real soon,it sure looked nice out on the river,and was prob fun dodging the icebergs....cheers

Yup somethings is wrong with the thumbnails..... I too have been having issues with them.... either warnings, or they wont open at all.... I have received a couple in PM's as well that just wouldnt work....   I think it is something the admins need to look into.  Ger.
is that Peche or downriver ?    bl

Awesome Buddy....let me know when you start marking fish.....should be any day now.....have the cousin coming over this weekend to fix my trailer and then hopefully I will be out with you dodging bergs!!!   Chrispy!
